Chapter Forty-Nine.	CHAPTER FORTY-NINE.	0.8421515
On Cauterizing Vitiligo.	On cauterization for leprosy.	0.68598044
If vitiligo becomes chronic and no medical remedy is effective against it, cauterize it with a slight depth, according to the thickness of the skin, until the whiteness disappears and its color changes.	When leprosy is of long standing and no device of medicine has any effect upon it, make a cauterization over it to a slight depth according to the thickness of the skin, until the whiteness has gone and the colour of the skin altered.	0.7837602
Then treat it with lentil flour, rose oil, plantain leaves, and pigeon blood or swallow blood, one part of each, mixed together and spread on a cloth, and applied to the area until it heals.	Then treat with lentil flour, oil of roses, arnoglossa leaves, and pigeons' or swallows' blood, of each equal parts mixed all together and spread on lint; let this stick to the place till healed.	0.9020447
